# AI Coding Fundamentals

- Preserve design quality; bad code gets more expensive with AI because speed amplifies entropy.
- Read before writing and follow the project’s existing patterns before inventing new ones.
- Align on the design concept before creating large plans, PRDs, or code.
- Use shared domain language and module names consistently.
- Work in small verified steps; feedback frequency is the speed limit.
- Prefer deep modules with simple interfaces over shallow webs of tiny pieces.
- Design interfaces deliberately; delegate implementation only behind tests and clear boundaries.
- Keep context lean: targeted reads, `@file` references, no pasted bulk files, concise outputs.
